Hello fellow NT staff!

§aClick on the checkbox to finish this first mission§r, and
the following objectives will §aguide you through how things work and advance in various ways§r.

§5Tinkers' Construct§r tools are way more §aversatile to use and create than vanilla tools§r, like with how you can mix n' match a tool's materials to make your tool have better §estats and traits§r.

If you are interested in learning about the world of Tinkers, then gain the following
items to complete the quest and to get started on making a §epersonalized tool for yourself§r.

(§7and if you are not interested, well... §c§4good luck with that§c§r)

Acquire some §6Iron Ingot§rs for tool forging.

§6Iron Ore§r spawns at §eY: 64§r to §eY: 3§r in the Overworld. Once you have found Iron, smelt it in a §6Furnace§r or throw the Ore block in the §3Smeltery§r and pour the iron into the §6Ingot Cast§r to §aobtain it's Ingot form§r.

First thing's first, get yourself some §6Woo§r§6d§r§r§r and make some wooden tools.
You can then use a §6Wooden Pickaxe§r to get yourself some stone and make some §astone tools§r.

Speaking of pickaxe...

Okay maybe I should've told you about the vanilla tools, that's on me gang :wilted_rose: :sob:.

Time to make your first pickaxe that won't break immediately.

§5§5§0§6§rFirst, you craft a §6Blank Pattern§r and use it on the §6§6Stencil Table§r. From there, you will be given a table of different patterns that §ayou can make the §§§aBlank Pattern into.

§rNormally your §c§a§e§e§6Tool Station§r will tell you what parts you need and what those parts look like. §9§1§2Let's make a pickaxe!§r To do this, we will need to make a §6Tool Rod Pattern§r, a §6Pickaxe Head Pattern§r, and a Binding Pattern. 

The§6 Part Builder§r will allow you to §aturn materials into usable tool parts from blank patterns§r. In the left box, add the pattern you want to use, then put the material (§7in our case, cobblestone§r) of your choice in one of the two boxes next to the pattern box. (§7Please note that some patterns may take more materials to make than others. Refer to the pattern's description to see it's material consumption§r).

And if you've done everything correctly, §ayou should get a (§7legit§a)§7 stone pickaxe!§r

§ecan be repaired§r by putting the tool in the Tool Station and putting the tool's material in
one of the slots around the middle one.

You can also use this to make yourself a §6Broadsword§r, a §6Hatchet§r, and §a§eother tools§r!

Pretty simple I'd say.

Using the knowledge you've learned from the §3Smeltery§r and §3Copper Tool§r quest, make yourself an §7§6Iron Pickaxe Head§r using a §6Pickaxe Head Cast§r.

If you need help, please refer to the §3Smeltery§r quest!

Now let's make a §6Copper Pickaxe Head§r, which we can then use to §emake Copper tools§r!

Once you have found Copper, throw the Ore block/ingot in the §3Smeltery§r and pour the Copper into the §6Pickaxe Head Cast§r to §aobtain a Copper Pickaxe Head for use in making a pickaxe§r.

While making stone tools is cool n' all, §anot all materials can be turned into tool parts with just the §6Part Builder§r. For example, §7Iron§r. To make iron into tool parts, we need to use the
§6§3§8§7§3Smeltery§r. To make one, refer to the §6Materials and You§6§r book on how to §a§ebuild the structure§r itself.

It really makes you say "§b§d§k§f§l§c§c§r§l§n§n§o§r§o§lI feel good§r §b§k§8§k§9§kad§6§kud§ca§kd§a§ku§e§kad§f§k§c§3§ka§kd§8§kuh§r". :O

(§7Also note that putting an ingot in place of the tool part can make the §6Ingot Cast§r§7, which will allow you to obtain the standard ingot version of the ore if the ore is not a gem. Useful for repairing your tools since those still take ingots to repair§r)

So you want to get the §3Smeltery§r? Nice choice kid.

§6Obsidian§r is a material that will ready you to get into a §ototally new dimension:§r

§4§lTHE NETHER §c:speaking_head: :fire:§r

The §6Draconic Core§r is a §o§lCORE§r element in the §5Draconic Evolution§r questline. It is used in multiple §5DE§r machines, fusion crafting recipes, etc.

To make the §rDraconic Core, you will need four §6Draconium Ingot§rs, four §6Enderium Ingot§rs, and one §6Infused Diamond§r.

Congratulations brotato, you have officially made it to one of the §cmost challenging mods§r in §7Factoriocraft§r: §5Draconic Evolution§r.

To get started with any §5DE§r features, you need to obtain §6Draconium Ingot§rs. To make Draconium Ingots, you need to §asmelt down §6Draconium Dust§r in a §6Furnace§r. You can get Draconium Dust by §amining §6Draconium Ore§r, which is an ore that §eonly spawns in space§r, so you §cwill not find it in the Overworld, the Nether, or the End§r.

(§7Note: you can also smelt down the Draconium Ore itself to get the ingot§r)

The §6Wyvern Core§r is an artifact that can be §eused in multiple crafting and fusion crafting recipes§r, even including it's §eown tool set§r.

To craft one, you will need four §6Draconium Ingot§rs, four §6Draconium Core§rs, and one §6Nether Star§r.

The §5§6Awakened Core§r is an artifact that is created through the §6Fusion Crafter§r and is important for §5Draconic Evolution§r.

To fusion craft the Awakened Core, you will need to §eput two §6Wyvern Core§r§es on both sides, with one side containing 3 §6Awakened Draconium Ingot§r§es and 2 on the other side§r. Then simply place a §6Nether Star§r in the §6Fusion Crafting Core§r.

(§7This sounds so familiar§r)

The §6Chaotic Core§r is a useful artifact in §ejust about every single §5Draconic Evolution§r §ecrafting recipe§r.

To fusion craft, you will need §atwo §6Awakened Core§es and two §6Awakened Draconium Ingot§es on both sides§r, and a §6Chaos Shard§r in the §6Fusion Crafting Core§r.

Pretty self-explanatory, I'd say.

Go §akill a Wither§r. To summon it, you will need four §6Soul Sand§r and three §6Wither Skeleton Skulls§r.

The §6Dragon's Heart§r is an item that can be obtained from §akilling the Ender Dragon§r. Please note that since most recipes §euse multiple hearts§r, you will need to §eresummon the Ender Dragon and defeat it again§r to keep on obtaining these. (§7To resummon the Ender Dragon, place four End Crystals on each side of the Exit Portal§))

The §cChaos Guardian§r is a Dragon §eguarding the §6Chaos Crystal§r. The §eChaos Island spawns throughout every 10,000 blocks§r in the End and will look like a regular End island that looks destroyed and is floating above the other islands.

We at §9NeoTechnologies§r do not know much about §cthis creature§r, but we do know that the §ecrystal is hidden inside the chaos island§r. While we don't know much about the Crystal itself, we do know that it's §cVERY unstable§r.

Good luck.

§4Be warned: It is recommended to have Draconic Gear when preparing to fight this beast, as calculations have shown that the beast itself is flowing with chaotic energy.§r

The §6Wyvern Fusion Crafting Injector§r is §eanother tier of the Fusion Injector block§r that §eallows for better crafting capabilities§r. Each tier can make §emore powerful items and upgrades§r.

To make one on the §6Fusion Crafter§r, you will need four §6Diamond§rs on the right, One §6Wyvern Core§r, §6Draconium Block§r, and two §6Draconium Core§rs on the left, and a §6Basic Fusion Crafting Injector§r in the Fusion Core.

The §6Draconic Fusion Crafting Injector§r is the next tier in the Fusion Injector tierlist. It is §erequired to have the §6Wyvern Fusion Crafting Injector§r§es to make this§r.

To fusion craft this, you will need two §6Wyvern Core§rs and two §6Diamond§rs on the left column, two Diamonds and an §6Awakened Draconium Block§r on the right, and an Wyvern Fusion Crafting Injector.

The §6Chaotic Fusion Crafting Injector§r is the §elast tier§r in the §eCrafting Injector tierlist§r. As such, it is §ecapable of the best fusion capabilities§r.


To make the Chaotic Fusion Crafting Injector in the §6Fusion Crafter§r, you will need two §6Diamond§rs and a §6Chaotic Core§r on the left column, and two Diamonds and a §6Dragon Egg§r on the right column, with a §6Draconic Fusion Crafting Injector§r in the Fusion Core.

The §6Basic Fusion Crafting Injector§r is another block §einvolved in the §6Fusion Crafter§e multiblock§r, as it serves as the §eleft and right column of the Crafter§r and can take one type of item for each injector.

To craft it, you will need five §6Obsidian§r, two §6Ionite Crystal§r, one §6§6Mica §7§7(Obtained from the §6§6Void Resource Miner§7§7)§r§r and a §6Draconic Core§r.

To make the Fusion Crafter, §eplace the Fusion Crafting Core in the middle§r, make §etwo plus signs out of the Injectors§r (§7facing towards the Crafting Core§r) and then §eplace them at most two blocks away from the Core§r. It doesn't matter where they are, they can be on the bottom and top or the left and right side of it.

Now that you have the basic shape down, §esupply all of the injectors with energy§r (§7You may need the §6Cryo-Stabilized Fluxduct§r§7 for the best transfer rate§r).

The §6Fusion Crafting Core§r is a key block in making the §6Fusion Crafter§r, a multi-block machine capable of §efusing together materials to create new ones§r. The Crafting Core is placed §eon the middle of the multi-block§r and is important for the §5DE§r quests later on.

To craft one, you will need four §6Pladium Block§rs (§7Obtained from the T3 §6Void Ore Miner§r§r), four §6Ionite Crystal§rs (§7Obtained from the T4 Void Ore Miner§r) and a §6Draconic Core§r.

The §6Wyvern Gear§r is the §efirst step into the §5Draconic Evolution§e gear§r, the second and last one being §aDraconic Tier§r.

This gear provides you protection with the §ahelp of RF-Powered Energy Shield§r. The gear are also §acharged with energy to be used properly§r. This enables you to §eavoid needing to spend materials and experience§r when repairing such item. To craft it, you'll need to unlock the §6Combination Crafting§r from §5Extended Crafting§r.

The §aWyvern Set of Armor§r needs the variants of many materials. 
This includes: 
- §6Iron§r, §6Gold§r, §6Diamond§r, 
- §6NanoSuit§r, §6QuantumSuit§r (§5IC2§r)
- §6Wither Bone§r (§5NetherEx§r)
- §6Tough Alloy§r, §6Hard Carbon§r (§5NuclearCraft§r)
- §6Dark Steel§r, §6Ender§r, §6Stellar§r (§5EnderIO§r)

and additional materials for base Wyvern Gears which are the §6Wyvern Core§r, §6Energy Core§r and the §6Draconium Ingot§rs.

The Wyvern Set of Tools on the other hand would need:
- Stellar Variant of the Tool (§7except §6Shovel§r)
- §6Draconic Core§r
- Wyvern Core
- §6Wyvern Energy Core§r
- Draconium Ingot

Crafting this will give you §agreater power§r in both §ehandling the Parasites and other rivals§r.

The §6Draconic Gear§r is the §elast tier of gears§r in §5Draconic Evolution§r.

This provides you the §eprevious abilities from your previous §6Wyvern Gear§r. However, Draconic Tier offers §ebetter stats in terms of damage or defense§r and §emay offer more abilities in some of the Tools and Armor§r. Examples includes, but not limited to §6Draconic Chestplate§r's §econfigurable creative flight§r.

An extra item has been added to the Fusion Crafting for the end-game experience which is the §6Tier Amazing Opinium Core§r from §5Extra Utilities 2§r.

Crafting this will prepare you for the great §4Chaos Guardian bossfight§r. §4Goodluck§r.

The §6Draconic Reactor Core§r is a reactor that emits §emassive amounts of energy§r.

To make the Draconic Reactor Core in fusion crafting, you will need §a§rtwo §6Awakened Core§e§rs and two §6Awakened Draconium Ingot§e§rs on both sides§r, and a §6Chaos Shard§r in the §6Fusion Crafting Core§r.

To make the §6Reactor Stabilizer§r in fusion crafting, you will need one §6Reactor Stabilizer Rotor Assembly§r, a §6Chaotic Core§r, and two Awakened Draconium Ingots on the left column, and a §6Reactor Stabilizer Focus Ring§r, a §6Draconic Energy Core§r, and two Awakened Draconium Ingots on the right side, with a §6Reactor Stabilizer Frame§r in the Fusion Crafting Core.

To make a Reactor Energy Injector in fusion crafting, you will need two §6Draconium Ingot§rs, two §6Iron Ingot§rs, and a §6Reactor Stabilizer Inner Rotor§r on the left column, and three Reactor Stabilizer Inner Rotors and two Draconium Ingots on the right column, with a §6Wyvern Core§r in the Fusion Crafting Core.

The T8 §6Energy Core§r is capable of §estoring nearly infinite amount of energy§r. As such, it is considered the §ebest and last task§r in the §5Draconic Evolution§r questline.

To craft the Energy Core, you will need two §6Wyvern Energy Core§rs, six §6Draconium Ingot§rs, and one §6Wyvern Core§r. To craft the §6Energy Core Stabilizer§r, you will need a §6Particle Generator§r and four §6Diamond§rs. To craft an §6Energy Pylon§r, you will need four Draconium Ingots, two §6Emerald§rs, one Diamond, one §6Eye of Ender§r, and a §6Draconic Core§r.

The §9true end-game of §7Factoriocraft Season 6§r...

If you have gotten here, this has truly shown your §etrue power§r and §edetermination§r throughout this season...

Are you ready for the §efinal questline§r? If so...
